oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Music book belonging to Julia M. Cable
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Book of music featuring various songs dating from the period of the Civil War. Songs include "The Sharpshooter's March"""Beauregard's Grand March"""Funeral March to the Memory of Abraham Lincoln"" the "Southern Belle Polka"""Camp Troubles! Hark the, Bugle Resounds"""Better Times are Coming" and more. Song book belonged to Ms. Julia M. Cable. Donor thinks Ms. Cable may have been born in 1843.
